			<dt ap-translate="INFO_USE.ORDER_TYPE01">Fixed Price Order : </dt>
			<dd ap-translate="INFO_USE.ORDER_TYPE01_CON">
                 Fixed price order is used when price is valued more than trade that is made on the trade contract. Hence when order is made after price is decided, that order is not made above the fixed buying price nor below the fixed selling price.
                 (Orders that are not made yet get maintained until BTC and KRW market orders are manually cancelled)

            </dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt ap-translate="INFO_USE.ORDER_TYPE02">Market Price Order : </dt>
			<dd ap-translate="INFO_USE.ORDER_TYPE02_CON">
